article.headline: Pierce nearly has triple-double in Celts' win
article.linkText: Magic lose sixth straight on the road
article.story:
BOSTON (AP) -- Paul Pierce nearly had a triple-double against what he rightfully called "the worst team in the league." Pierce had 19 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists, and Mike James added 21 points in leading the Boston Celtics past Orlando 101-93 Wednesday night to extend the Magic's losing streak to six games. "It is easy to go out against the worst team in the league and do what we did," Pierce said. "But this was a must-win, and any win feels good right now." After trailing 90-72 with 8:16 remaining, Orlando went on a 14-2 run featuring three 3-pointers and 11 points by Tracy McGrady. But the Magic got no closer as Pierce scored four straight points to make it 96-86. "The Celtics made plays down the stretch," Magic coach Johnny Davis said. "We kept closing in, but they kept giving an answer to our runs." McGrady scored 28 points to lead Orlando, which has lost six straight on the road and has the league's worst record (8-28). He had 14 points in the fourth quarter. Keith Bogans added a career-high 18 points. "We had to key on McGrady because we knew how easy it is for him to get hot," James said. Boston opened the fourth quarter with 10 straight points to go ahead 90-72. "We dug a hole we couldn't get out of," McGrady said. "We played a much better second half than first, but we have to put two halves together." Chris Mihm made his first start for Boston since being acquired from Cleveland 12 games ago and had 11 points and 11 rebounds. "I'm trying to fit in and be a big piece of this team," Mihm said. "Teams are going to make their runs and we need to be mentally tough to hold them off." Eight different Celtics scored in the first quarter and Boston shot 16-of-25 to take a 36-29 lead. Boston increased the lead to 50-35 with 6:40 remaining in the half on Mark Blount's dunk. Pierce also had nine turnovers for the Celtics, who snapped a three-game home losing streak. Lue had 10 points and nine assists, while Juwan Howard added 13 points and eight rebounds for the Magic.

Game notes
Pierce received a technical foul with 6:29 remaining in the third when he threw the ball the length of the court after being called for traveling on consecutive possessions. When the game ended, Pierce kicked the ball 30 rows into the crowd. ... Celtics forward Vin Baker served the first game of his three-game suspension for noncompliance with his treatment program. ... The Magic have allowed over 100 points in four straight games. ... Lue has 27 assists in his last three games despite averaging 3.6 per game.
